    "updated_at": "2014-10-16T15:59:26Z",
    "body": "It seems `gtk_menu_proxy_get()` function does no longer exist.\n\nTypically, when you've this kind bug (that you could have with Eclipse, Filezilla, etc.), you will find a solution which say that you've to unset `$UBUNTU_MENUPROXY`.\n\nAnother way to detect if this menu proxy is running is to check if `libappmenu.so` is running but it's maybe not the best solution. Or we can maybe check if `com.canonical.AppMenu.Registrar` bus is available.\n"
